# gen77: self-model introspection depth. Internal predicates are filtered
# so "what do you know?" shows only user-facing knowledge.
# Start with zero user-facing facts.
> what do you know?
< I know 0 fact(s) across 0 predicate(s). Ask me about a specific topic.
> how many facts do you know?
< I know 0 fact(s).
> what predicates do you know?
< I don't know any predicates yet.
> show me your knowledge
< I know 0 fact(s) total.
# Teach some facts and re-query.
> rex is a dog
< Learned: dog(rex).
> fido is a dog
< Learned: dog(fido).
> every dog is a mammal
< Learned rule: mammal(X) :- dog(X).
# Direct facts only: dog(rex), dog(fido). mammal is rule-derived.
> what do you know?
< I know 2 fact(s) across 1 predicate(s). Ask me about a specific topic.
> how many facts do you know?
< I know 2 fact(s).
> what predicates do you know?
< I know these predicates: dog.
> show me your knowledge
< Here is everything I know: dog(rex). dog(fido).
# Identity and capability still work.
> who are you?
< I am parrot0.
> what can you do?
< I can answer questions about facts and rules, do simple arithmetic, reason about cause and effect, compare quantities, tell whether two things are the same, remember things you tell me, read a short passage and pull out facts, track what a pronoun refers to, continue a sequence you teach me, remember what we talked about.
